<HEADLINE> Kazakh Prime Minister Replaced Temporarily for Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan President
Nursultan Nazarbayev issued a decree today appointing First Deputy
Prime Minister Akhmetzhan Esimov to act temporarily as prime
minister as Prime Minister Akezhan Kazhegeldin is suffering from
illness.
</P>
<P>
Kazhegeldin, 45, left Alma-Ata today to receive further
medical treatment abroad after the ailment of his shank turned
worse, the Kazakh Telegraph Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Kazhegeldin, who took office in October, 1994, has been
receiving treatment in the Kazakh central hospital since
mid-August, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
