<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Grants Albania 1.87m ECU in Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
executive agency of the 15-nation European Union, today granted
1.87 million ECUs (1.68 million US dollars) worth of aid to
Albania.
</P>
<P>
The aid, to be managed by the European Community Humanitarian
Office, will enable non-governmental organizations to carry out
coordinated actions over the next six months in the Balkan country
that has just come out of several months of civil unrest.
</P>
<P>
The package of aid will provide food for vulnerable groups in
places that have been inaccessible to date. It also provides the
medical supplies that are lacking in many hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Albania is still suffering from the consequences of a crisis
that led to widespread lawlessness and the security situation is
still precarious though the Italy-led multinational protection
force, which was dispatched in mid-April to safeguard deliveries
of humanitarian aid, is now withdrawing.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the aid program of the European Community
Humanitarian Office are the World Health Organization and
non-governmental organizations from Italy, Greece and France.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
