<HEADLINE> Russia Continues to Oppose NATO Expansion: Sergeyev </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Russian Minister of Defense
Igor Dmitriyevich Sergeyev reiterated here that Russia will
continue its opposition to North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO)'s eastward expansion.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev made the remarks to the press after meeting his
Swedish counterpart Bjorn Von Sydow today.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two discussed the European security
issue and signed a joint declaration of intention on further
military cooperation between their countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Russia prepares this year to add specific contents to the
documents regarding the Russia-NATO relations and tackle some
disturbing issues through negotiations, said Sergeyev.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish defense minister arrived here yesterday, starting a
four-day visit to Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
