<HEADLINE> Israel to Maintain Good Relations with Jordan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Israel will maintain its
good relations with Jordan despite the shooting incident occurred
today in Amman, Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai said.
</P>
<P>
Reacting to the shooting incident in which two Israeli
Embassy security guards in Amman were injured, Mordechai also
said today in Beer Yaakov, near Tel Aviv, that he expects
Jordanian security forces to act forcefully against terrorists.
</P>
<P>
According to the Israeli Foreign Ministry, the two Israeli
Embassy security guards were shot this morning outside the
Israeli Embassy in Amman by some unknown gunmen and were lightly
injured.
</P>
<P>
Mordechai said that he has instructed the Israeli Embassy in
Amman to cooperate closely with the Jordanian side in handling
with this matter and waiting for the full report about the
incident.
</P>
<P>
Jordanian police stepped up security around the Israeli
Embassy in Amman after the attack. 
