<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets Chilean Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The friendly
cooperation between China and Chile in various areas has been
going smoothly and satisfactorily, noted Chinese and Chilean
senior officials here today.
</P>
<P>
Qian Qichen, vice-premier and foreign minister of China, spoke
highly of the growth of relations between the two countries in his
meeting with Chilean Foreign Minister Jose Miguel Insulza this
morning at the United Nations headquarters in New York.
</P>
<P>
The friendly cooperation between the two nations has been going
very healthily and their two-way trade has been growing so rapidly
that Chile has become China's second largest trade partner in
Latin America now, said Qian.
</P>
<P>
China and Chile, both of which are Pacific ridge nations, have
good cooperation in the Asian-Pacific Economic Cooperation and on
other international affairs, Qian added.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice-premier expressed thanks to Chile for its
support to China on the latter's accession to the World Trade
Organization, the American Development Bank and in other areas. He
hoped the two countries would further cooperate in the world
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Insulza expressed his congratulations on the successful
conclusion of the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China. He said he has the confidence that the congress would bring
an important and deep influence to the development in China.
</P>
<P>
He agreed with Qian on the friendly ties between the two
countries and said he expected a good prospect in their
cooperation in the fields of economy, trade and science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean foreign minister also said the two countries should
continue their mutual understanding and support in international
affairs.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting, Qian invited his Chilean counterpart to
visit China and the latter, while expecting an earlier trip to
China, invited Qian to tour Chile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
