<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has called on the
international community to continue assisting eastern and central
African countries in their search for peace in Burundi through the
process of political dialogue.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made by Jakaya Kikwete, Minister for Foreign Affairs
and International Cooperation in his address to the 52nd session of
the United Nations General Assembly in New York, according to a press
released by the Foreign Ministry here today.
</P>
