interest in Burundi but to help as reaffirmed by the September 4 Dar
es Salaam summit at which the leaders of the region had reiterated
their commitment to peace in Burundi and called on the military
regime in Burundi to abandon the course of confrontation and seek
dialogue and political accommodation.
</P>
<P>
The Burundi political crisis which was triggered by the
assassination of the country's first elected President Melchior
Ndadaye in 1993 reached a new turn in July 1996 following a military
coup that brought Major Pierre Buyoya to power after toppling a
civilian government of President Sylvester Ntibantunganya.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of eastern and central African countries have been making
efforts to search for ways to restore peace in Burundi. 
</P>
