<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Tourism
Commission said today it will promote tourism in the country to
earn more hard currency.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference here in connection with the World
Tourism Day to be celebrated on September 27, commissioner of the
organization Yusuf Abdullahi said the number of tourists has
dramatically increased during the past few years owing to political
stability and economic reforms in the country.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, it is not satisfactory when compared with
the variety, beauty and high quantity of the tourist
attractions that the country is blessed with.
</P>
<P>
