<HEADLINE> Turkey Wishes to Normalize Ties with Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Turkey said today that it is
willing to normalize its relations with Syria so long as certain
conditions are met.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a weekly press conference here, Turkish Foreign
Ministry Deputy Spokesman Sermet Atacanli said that it was
Damascus' support for the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK)
that stands in the way of the normalization of the
Turkish-Syrian relations.
</P>
<P>
Syria has to give up its support for the PKK if it wants to
develop close ties with Turkey, Atacanli said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Turkey hoped to enhance its cooperation with
Syria and this stance has remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Syria have shared a bitter relationship due to the
PKK issue, the dispute over the water resources of the Euphrates
as well as other sensitive issues.
</P>
<P>
Recently, Damascus accused Ankara of taking part in the joint
naval war games with Israel and the United States to be held in
November in eastern Mediterranean, saying the maneuvers are
directed against Syria.
</P>
<P>
However, Turkey has been trying to assure its Arab neighbors
that the tripartite exercises are not directed against any other
country, saying that it is "a search-and-rescue operation" devoid
of any strategic importance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
