<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Calls For Study Of Party Congress Documents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China's Central Committee, told a meeting of the Central
Committee's Organization Department today that an effort must be
made to bring the tasks set by the Party's National Congress to
the nation's attention.
</P>
<P>
"A conscientious attitude is needed to study the documents of
the Party's 15th National Congress and to follow its guiding
principles," he said, pointing to the Congress as a historical
milestone in the development of China and the Party.
</P>
<P>
General Secretary Jiang Zemin summarized the Party's experience
gained since the Third Plenary Session of the 11th Central
Committee in 1978, at the Congress, and it embodies the Party's
collective wisdom, Hu explained.
</P>
<P>
He said that holding the banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory high is
the key to studying the documents and adhering to the basic line
of the primary stage of socialism. In doing so, a hard effort must
be made to get a good grasp of Jiang's report and its key areas,
he noted.
</P>
<P>
Practical steps should be taken to solve remaining
contradictions and problems coming from economic and social
activities to push reforms and opening-up and the modernization
drive into the 21st century, he said.
</P>
<P>
A consistent, strong, and improved Party leadership is
essential to meeting the goals set forth at the Congress, and most
importantly, an effort must be made to arm the whole Party,
especially leading officials, with Deng Xiaoping Theory to use it
as the guiding ideology, Hu stressed.
</P>
<P>
Policies have been worked out, and cadres are the dominant
factor in implementing them, so it is important that the work of
leading bodies at all levels be improved to provide a strong
organizational guarantee to the great cause of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics, Hu concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
