<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Military Prosecutors Probe into Cairo Bus Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Egyptian military
prosecution today started investigations into last Thursday's
fatal attack on a tourist bus in central Cairo that killed 10
people and injured seven others.
</P>
<P>
A judicial source said the military prosecutors took over the
case's file from the state security Monday night after a decree
issued by President Hosni Mubarak last weekend that ordered the
case be taken over by a military tribunal.
</P>
<P>
Two suspects, Saber Mohamed Farahat and his brother Mahmoud
Farahat, had been arrested for the shooting and petrol bomb attack
on a tourist bus, which killed nine German tourists and an
Egyptian driver in central Cairo at noon on September 18.
</P>
<P>
The military prosecution will begin by looking into the
investigations carried out by the state security with the two
suspects and their accomplices who have forwarded them with the
ammunition and aided one of them to escape the mental hospital he
was committed to.
</P>
<P>
The case is expected to be referred in October to a military
judiciary court, where cases are usually expected to have a speedy
trial. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
