<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Steps Up Fight Against Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Canada's customs agency
hopes to build three specialized warehouses at three major ports
as part of its stepped-up anti-smuggling campaign, a report said
today.
</P>
<P>
The Canada Customs said about 60 percent of the illegal
contraband it seizes, ranging from drugs, weapons to pornography,
has come from containers entering Halifax, Montreal and Vancouver
ports.
</P>
<P>
Customs agents have found nearly 2.1 billion U.S. dollars in
drugs among the millions of the containers entering Canada.
</P>
<P>
The Canada Customs is trying to boost its inspections to about
three percent of all containers entering Canada, a fifteen-fold
increase from 1989.
</P>
<P>
"Containers pose the highest risk because of the volumes and
their size," said an official of the agency.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations are now under way between the agency and Canadian
shippers on the proposals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970923.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Intertoto Format May Attract Big Clubs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- A new Intertoto Cup format
may entice European soccer's big clubs who currently ignore what
they consider a summer inconvenience, UEFA officials said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Changes being proposed include abolishing the current league
format and replacing it with a home-and-away, knock-out
competition.
</P>
<P>
German and French clubs have supported the competition since it
was revamped in 1994 but bigger clubs from countries like England,
Italy and Spain have shown little interest.
</P>
<P>
UEFA thinks they might be enticed into entering if they had to
play just two, or at most four, matches in August to gain a
back-door entry into European club competition.
</P>
<P>
Among the proposals is an idea that teams from smaller
countries would play a series of knockout rounds. They would
eventually meet, for example, an English or Italian club, exempt
from the earlier stages, in a final round.
</P>
<P>
The winner of that tie would qualify for the UEFA Cup.
</P>
<P>
The idea is still being discussed by UEFA and European pools
companies who originally organised the Intertoto many years ago as
a way of providing revenue during the summer months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970923.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Svorada Wins 17th Stage in Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Czech rider Jan Svorada won
the 17th stage over 182.7 kilograms from Santander to Burgos at
the Tour of Spain cycling race on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
German Marcel Wust, who has also won three stages in this race,
pulled his right foot out of his pedal clip in the last 25 meters
and was second for the second successive day.
</P>
<P>
Fellow German Sven Teutenberg was third, just ahead of a large
group of riders who finished one minute and 38 seconds clear of
the rest of the field.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland's Alex Zuelle kept the overall lead. 
</P>
