<HEADLINE> UNDP to provide fund for Pakistan's Country Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Board of
United Nations Development Program(UNDP) has approved to provide a
fund of 61.19 million U.S. dollars for Pakistan's Country Program,
a news release issued here today by the UNDP said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's Country Program is consistent with UNDP's corporate
strategy of poverty eradication through sustainable human
development, said the release.
</P>
<P>
The release said that the money was for a period of six years
from 1998 to 2003.
</P>
<P>
To support the implementation of the program, said the release,
UNDP is establishing a Program Support and Management Program to
support the increasingly decentralized implementation of UNDP's
co-operation in the country. 
