<HEADLINE> Homeless Palestinians Ask Czech President for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Homeless Palestinians in
Jerusalem sent a letter today to visiting Czech President Vaclav
Havel, asking him to help improve their conditions through
mediation with Israelis.
</P>
<P>
The letter was handed over by the Committee of the Camp of
Steadfasting and Endurance. The camp, set up in the Siwaneh
quarter of Jerusalem, now houses the Palestinians whose homes were
demolished by Israel.
</P>
<P>
The letter urged Havel to help achieve a just and humane
solution that could help end the sufferings of the homeless
Palestinians in the camp.
</P>
<P>
Every minute, Israel is practicing an apartheid racist policy
among Arab citizens in Jerusalem, the letter said.
</P>
<P>
Israel has denied building permits to Palestinians in Jerusalem
and 70,000 Palestinians have been affected by such policies, the
letter said.
</P>
<P>
Havel arrived here Monday for an official visit and is
scheduled to meet both Israeli and Palestinian leaders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
