<HEADLINE> Chinese, Ukrainian Chiefs Of General Staff Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- General Fu Quanyou, Chief of
General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), met
today with general Aleksander Zatynaiko, Chief of General Staff of
the Ukrainian Armed Forces.
</P>
<P>
Zatynaiko is the first Ukrainian Chief of General Staff to
visit China since Ukraine's independence.
</P>
<P>
Fu said he believes the visit will help strengthen mutual
understanding, friendship and co-operation between the two
countries' armed forces and promote all-round bilateral friendly
relations.
</P>
<P>
He briefed the Ukrainian visitor on China's defense policy and
army building and noted that General Secretary Jiang Zemin
announced at the Chinese Communist Party's 15th National Congress
the downsizing of the PLA by 500,000 people within three years.
</P>
<P>
"This is not only an important step of improving the PLA's
quality but also an action to safeguard world peace and regional
security and stability," he said.
</P>
<P>
The PLA will firmly implement that decision, Fu added.
</P>
<P>
Zatynaiko said he believes that his China visit will further
increase bilateral military co-operation, especially in military
technology.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed Fu on the Ukrainian armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Fu held a welcoming ceremony for Zatynaiko
and his party, who arrived here yesterday on an official good-will
visit at Fu's invitation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
