<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Somali Faction Leader to be Expelled from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The cabinet ministers of
the break away republic of Somaliland have unanimously approved
the expulsion of Abdurahman Ahmed Ali Tuur, deputy President of
Hussein Aidid's self-crowned government, from Somaliland within
24 hours starting from this morning.
</P>
<P>
A statement announced last night by Abdi Iddiris Duale, press
secretary of the president of the break away republic of
Somaliland, said the approval of the expulsion came after Tuur
failed to recognize the sovereignty and the independence of
Somaliland Republic.
</P>
<P>
Tuur and his delegation reached Hargeisa, capital of the
Somaliland three days ago where they were warmly welcomed and had
lunch with Mohamed Hagi Ibrahim Egal, president of the break away
republic.
</P>
<P>
The statement further noted that after serious talks, Turr
still insisted his position of seeking a federal system with
southern Somalia rather than accepting the secession of
Somaliland.
</P>
<P>
Duale said Egal and his cabinet ministers have understood that
the presence of Tuur in Hargeisa is endangering the security of
the whole republic and the unity of the people in Somaliland.
</P>
<P>
The statement said Tuur will be sent back to Mogadishu.
There's no word yet from Tuur himself over the new situation, but
he is still in Hargeisa with his large delegation.
</P>
<P>
The statement also said Egal, president of the unrecognized
break away republic of Somaliland, has rejected a request from
Tuur to meet him privately. There's doubt that there will be a
forceful expulsion and it is not yet clear where Tuur will go
from Hargeisa, either to the town of Buro which is his home town,
or straight back to Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
This expulsion might create a new wave of violence in
Somaliland despite Tuur's denial that he went there to make
trouble. Tuur still enjoys the support of quite a large number of
militiamen from his Garhajis sub-clan who are scattered in the
Southern Hawd (forest) reserve area of Somaliland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
