<DOCNO> XIE19970923.0098 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-US Co-operation In Satellite Launch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The China Great Wall Industry
Corporation signed a contract today with the Loral Space and
Communications Co. of the United States on launching a US-made
telecommunications satellite that will serve China and its
neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
The satellite, China SAT-8, will be carried by a Long March-3B
rocket, which has a larger loading capacity than any other
Chinese-made carrier rockets, with a five-ton payload on the
synchronous orbit of the Earth.
</P>
<P>
The SAT-8 is equipped with 53 transponders, 36 of which use the
C wave band and the others the Ku band. After being launched into
the orbit, the satellite will be transfered to and operated by the
China Telecommunications and Broadcasting Satellite Company. It
will provide telecommunications, television, and other broadcast
services for China and its neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
The satellite is scheduled to be launched in the fourth quarter
of 1998.
</P>
<P>
China has had five successful satellite launches since last
October, using Long March-3B rockets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
