<DOCNO> XIE19970923.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-23 14:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq Hopes to Renew Ties with Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Foreign Minister
Mohammed Saeed al-Sahhaf has voiced his country's wishes to
restore diplomatic relations with Syria in the near future, Iraqi
newspaper Al-Iraq reported today.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that diplomatic relations between Iraq and Syria will
be reestablished in the near future, and that bilateral ties
... will expand for their common benefit." the paper quoted
al-Sahhaf as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Our relations with Syria are for the time being limited to
reopening the joint border with the aim of promoting trade ties
and exchange of goods between the two countries," al-Sahhaf said.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi-Syrian ties, severed in early 1980's because of Syria's
support for Iran in the Iraqi-Iranian War from 1980 to 1988, have
been improved in recent months.
</P>
<P>
The two countries reopened the border in June and later signed
an agreement for Iraq to import goods from Syria within the
framework of the oil-for-food deal between the United Nations and
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Iraqi foreign minister also expressed the hope
that consultations between Iraq and Iran would resume for the
normalization of bilateral relations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
