<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, Italy Sign Two Grant Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The governments of
Ethiopia and Italy signed here today two specific grant
agreements amounting to 4.45 million U.S. Dollars, a press
release from the Ministry of Economic Development and Cooperation
of Ethiopia said.
</P>
<P>
The press release reported that the grant is mainly for rural
infrastructure and basic services rehabilitation as well as
development projects in Amhara and Oromia regions of Ethiopia.
