<P>
Of the total grant, 2.02 million US Dollars is allocated to
support rural infrastructure, basic services rehabilitation and
development in north Wollo of Amhara region. The grant is aimed
at increasing the level of food security, slowing the process of
environmental degradation and supporting the resettlement of
population at risk.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 2.43 million Dollars is earmarked for the pilot
agricultural development scheme in the Oromia region.
</P>
<P>
The specific grant agreements were part of the follow up of
the framework of cooperation agreements signed by the two
governments in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
