<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-23 12:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suicide Bombers Come From Palestinian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu reiterated today that the suicide bombers who
struck two central Jerusalem markets came from the Palestinian
self-rule areas despite the denial by the Palestinian National
Authority (PNA).
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a joint news conference with visiting Czech
President Vaclav Havel, Netanyahu said that Israel is much more
certain now that the perpetrators of the July 30 bombings in
Mahane Yehuda market and the September 4 bombings in Ben Yehuda
mall came from the Palestinian areas instead of abroad as the PNA
claims.
</P>
<P>
He added that Israeli security forces are still investigating
the two bombings in order to identify the suicide bombers.
</P>
<P>
Saying Israel is on high alert against more terrorist attacks,
Netanyahu demanded the PNA honor its commitments to the Oslo
accords by fighting terrorist organizations and their support
infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
He praised Jordan for making 100 percent efforts to fight
terror, although it could not get 100 percent results. He was
apparently referring to the Monday terrorist attack against Israeli
guards at the Israeli embassy in Amman, during which two
guards were wounded by a previously unknown anti-Israeli Islamic
group.
</P>
<P>
"This is what we expect from Mr. (Yasser) Arafat and the
Palestinian Authority: to fight terrorists and not embrace them,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Despite the recent wave of terrorist attacks in Israel that
seemed to have smashed Netanyahu's election promises to achieve
peace with security, the Israeli leader insisted it is still
possible to wipe out terrorism.
</P>
<P>
"I don't think we will be able to affect the terrorists'
mentality, I think we can certainly affect their capabilities,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Israeli Army intelligence chief Moshe Yaalon said
today that the suicide bombers of the recent two terrorist
attacks in Jerusalem came from Area B under Israeli security
control, but those who planned and ordered the attacks are
from Area A under sole PNA control.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the Knesset (Parliament) Foreign Affairs and
Defense Committee, Yaalon said that the breakthrough in probing
the bombings was achieved thanks to the recent massive arrests
of Palestinian suspects in the Nablus area.
</P>
<P>
Since the two Jerusalem bombing attacks which killed 20
people in addition to five suicide bombers, Israeli security
forces have arrested over 600 Palestinians suspected of being
involved in terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Only in the single operation last Saturday night, 40
Palestinians were nabbed by Israeli security forces for being
affiliated with the militant Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas),
which claimed responsibility for the two Jerusalem attacks.
</P>
<P>
In reaction to the Israeli claim about the indentities of the
suicide bombers, the PNA leader Arafat demanded days ago that
Netanyahu provide evidence to prove the Israeli claim.
</P>
<P>
Ahmed Pibi, adviser to Arafat on Israeli affairs, charged
Netanyahu today for misleading the public by claiming that the
terrorists came from the Palestinian areas. He said that the next
few days would prove that the opposite is true. 
</P>
</TEXT>
