<HEADLINE> Islamic Fundamentalists Kill 85, Wound 67 in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Islamic fundamentalist rebels
killed 85 civilians and wounded 67 others overnight Monday in a
suburb of Algiers, Algerian security forces said.
</P>
<P>
At least 31 of the wounded were in serious condition in the
massacre in Bentoumi-Bentalha area in Baraki district of the
capital, the second worst single slaughter in more than five years
of battle between the Islamic Salvation Front and government
troops, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Security forces said that "a group of terrorists" killed the 85
people "in a cowardly way", which was the Algerian term for
killing people by cutting their throats, according to the Algerian
news agency APS.
</P>
<P>
But an AFP report quoted survivors as saying on Tuesday the
death toll was between 180 and 200.
</P>
<P>
Ninety-eight people were killed less than a month ago in the
worst single massacre since the government called off an election
in January, 1992. 
</P>
