<HEADLINE> U.S. Airforce Plane Catches Fire When Landing in Crete </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. airforce P-3 aircraft
skidded off the landing runway and caught fire after its left wheel
broke at Souda airbase in the southern Greek island of Crete early
today.
</P>
<P>
Its two left engines and left wing were also damaged, but none
of the six-member crew were hurt in the accident, the Greek Airforce
General Staff announced.
</P>
<P>
The four-engine plane was taking part in a NATO southeastern wing
exercise code-named "dynamic mix." 
</P>
</TEXT>
