<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Trade Deficit Reduced Sharply This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's foreign trade deficit
dropped to 1.67 billion U.S. dollars in the first eight months of
this year, 44.3 percent lower than that of the same period last
year, local press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The decrease is mainly attributed to a rapid increase in
exports, with ten main export lines having stable markets in the
world and to a three percent decrease in import between January
and August, compared to the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, imports of August were 13 percent lower than those
of July, with priorities given to imports of modern machinery and
equipment and limits on imports of automobiles, motorbikes and
steel.
</P>
<P>
Also during this period, import value of consumer goods made up
5 percent of the total import turnover. Import and export duties
reached 8,400 billion dong (711.86 million dollars), said the
reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
