<HEADLINE> Lagos Varsity Expels 49 for Cultist Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- In a continued battle against
cultism at the University of Lagos, the authorities of the
institute have expelled 49 students.
</P>
<P>
A statement signed by Registrar of the university Wale
Aderibigbe Monday also declared the suspension of six students,
while 18 others serving suspension had their penalties lifted.
</P>
<P>
The statement further disclosed that all expelled students
were being referred to the police for furthergbe actions, adding
that the pardoned students were to remain under close monitoring
and surveillance.
</P>
<P>
It also advised the expelled students "in their own interest
not to enter the university campus to avoid being apprehended and
dealt in accordance with the law".
</P>
<P>
Cultists activities, which are on the rise recently in the
country's institutions of higher learning, claimed the lives of
two undergraduates of the university earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
Police has since begun petrolling around the campus in a bid
to avoid renewed clashes between rival cultist groups, and
investigations have been underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
