<HEADLINE> China's Satellite Communication Firm Issues Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing-headquartered
Citic Guo'an Information Industry Co. Ltd Monday became the first
Chinese listed company in satellite communications when it issued
50 million A shares for domestic investors through the Shenzhen
Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The shares were priced at 7.09 yuan per unit and the funds of
343 million yuan, raised through the issue, will be invested in
four projects, including the expansion of one satellite
communication network.
</P>
<P>
The issue is sponsored by Citic Guo'an Corporation, a
subsidiary of the China International Trust and Investment
Corporation (Citic). Its business includes satellite
communications, network projects, information transmission, wire
television, mobile communications, and advertising.
</P>
<P>
The Citic Guo'an Satellite Communication Network, which opened
in July 1992, offers a wide range of services including language
and data transmission and computer networking. The planned
expansion will make it China's second largest satellite
communication network.
</P>
<P>
Currently China has dozens of special-purpose satellite
communication networks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
