<HEADLINE> Model Families Commended in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- One hundred families across
China were commended here today as models in a national drive to
promote moral standards in families.
</P>
<P>
Ten won special awards as outstanding representatives of the
100 families in today's commendation event, which is the
culmination of the drive to create "civilized families" launched
last November by 18 state ministries and commissions, including
the Propaganda Department of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
Central Committee, the All-China Women's Federation (ACWF), and
the Ministry of Civil Affairs.
</P>
<P>
The families were honored for carrying on the Chinese tradition
of respecting the old and caring for the young, respecting the
equality of the sexes and preserving harmony between husband and
wife, managing the household in an industrious and thrifty way,
and promoting neighborliness.
</P>
<P>
In a speech at today's event, Chen Muhua, Vice-Chairwoman of
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress and ACWF
Chairwoman, said: "These model families both retain the fine
tradition of the Chinese nation, and represent the characteristics
of the socialist civilization."
</P>
<P>
When the Chinese society is in a period of transition, she
pointed out, problems concerning familial ethics arise, making it
all the more necessary to promote moral standards for families.
</P>
<P>
Chen emphasized that promotion of familial ethics is beneficial
to not only family harmony and stability, but also the improvement
of national quality, promotion of economic development and social
progress.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen, member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee and head of the Propaganda Department of the CPC Central
Committee; and Peng Peiyun, State Councillor and chief of the
Working Committee on Women and Children under the State Council
attended today's conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
