<HEADLINE> Huangpu (Whampoa) Alumni Learn Gist of 15th Party Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Some alumni of the Huangpu
(Whampoa) Military Academy established by Dr. Sun Yat-sun, the
forerunner of the Chinese revolution, have called on alumni both
at home and abroad to make more contributions to national
reunification.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-based alumni made the call at a forum on the study
of the just-ended 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Mo Wenhua, vice chief of the Huangpu Military Academy Alumni
Association and a special delegate to the Congress, presided over
the forum.
</P>
<P>
He said that CPC General Secretary Jiang Zemin in his report to
the congress voiced his wish that the Chinese people on both sides
of the Taiwan Strait will work together for national reunification
and rejuvenation. His report expressed the common aspirations of
all Huangpu alumni and their friends and relations, Mo said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's smooth return marked a significant step toward
national reunification, and the post-return situation proved that
the "one country, two systems" theory not only suits Hong Kong,
but Taiwan as well, said Mo.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the Taiwan authorities' attempts to create
"two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan" run counter to the
historical trend for national reunification and the common wishes
of all the Chinese people. He urged the Taiwan authorities to stop
separatist activities and return to the "one China" stand.
</P>
<P>
Other alumni attending the forum asked that fellow alumni and
their friends and relations both at home and abroad heed Jiang's
call, and do more to ensure peaceful unification of the motherland
by promoting cross-strait economic, scientific and cultural
exchange and cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
