<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ramos Accepts Resignation of Railways Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos today accepted the resignation of Philippine National
Railways General Manager Jose Dado after a deadly train collision
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The resignation will be effective from September 24 and Ramos
has designated Assistant General Manager Rafael Mosura as acting
general manager.
</P>
<P>
Ramos' acceptance of Dado's resignation was contained in a
handwritten order to Transportation Secretary Arturo Enrile
following the train collision at the Bicutan-Sucat area in
Muntinlupa city, south of Manila.
</P>
<P>
The collision, which killed nine people and injured some 300
others, was one of the country's worst railway accidents in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
Upon learning of the accident Monday, President Ramos
immediately directed the Department of Transportation and the
National Disaster Coordinating Council to undertake joint
operations to provide the needed assistance to the victims.
</P>
<P>
Ramos also ordered the department to restore train services and
"ensure the full safety of the entire line."  
</P>
</TEXT>
