<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Anti-Corruption Drive Successful, Says Report (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- China's anti-corruption
campaign has produced remarkable results since the 14th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) in 1992, according
to the Party's top disciplinary body.
</P>
<P>
The nation has worked out an effective way to battle corruption
while building socialism with Chinese characteristics, the CPC
Central Commission for Discipline Inspection said in its work
report, which was earlier submitted to the newly-concluded 15th
Party Congress for approval.
</P>
<P>
The central collective leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core
has considered improving the work style of the Party, building up
a clean government and countering corruption as "an issue that
concerns the survival or death of the Party and the state" and has
achieved a lot in this regard over the past five years, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
Some 263,000 officials at or above the county (section) level
made self-evaluations for rule and discipline violations between
1993 and last June, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The nation's disciplinary and supervisory agencies investigated
731,000 corruption cases and solved 670,100 of them between
October 1992 and June 1997, and took disciplinary or
administrative action against 669,300 party members. A total of
121,500 members were expelled from the Party, among whom 37,492
were punished for their criminal acts.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970923.0167 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Anti-Corruption Drive Successful, Says Report (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Over the years China has also succeeded in rectifying unhealthy
practices in various departments and sectors. Professional ethics
and the moral standards of Party officials have improved, and a
number of laws and regulations on improving the work style of the
Party and building up a clean government have been formulated.
</P>
<P>
Based on a summarization of years of experience, the report
said that the anti-corruption campaign must closely center around
economic development and serve the best interests of the whole
Party and the entire nation.
</P>
<P>
The report also said that to push forward the anti-corruption
in a healthy and orderly manner, the leadership of the Party must
be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
In spite of the success, anti-corruption is a complex,
difficult and protracted struggle, as corruption has not been
brought under complete control and is still spreading within some
parts of the Party, government and judicial system, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The spread of corruption within the Party and government and
among officials must be eradicated in five years, it vowed.
</P>
<P>
To this end, greater efforts must be made to guarantee the
effective implementation of the Party's lines, principles and
policies, strengthen the leadership, improve education in Party
spirit, work style and discipline, and increase disciplinary
examination, the report pointed out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
