<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seminar on Cervantes Opens in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Asia's first international
seminar on Spanish writer Miguel De Cervantes opened today in
Nanjing, capital of east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of scholars from Spain, Germany, Britain, Brazil, the
US, Italy and China, as well as the Spanish ambassador to China,
attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
"The meeting will be a historical event of great significance
to be remembered by the academic circle," said Chen Kaixian, a
professor from Nanjing University.
</P>
<P>
Cervantes, the father of the modern Spanish novel, is famous
for the book "Don Quixote." The book was first translated into
Chinese in 1922 as part of the "New Culture Movement," which
advocated learning from Western literature.
</P>
<P>
In May, China published the complete works of Cervantes to mark
the 450th birthday of the renowned writer.
</P>
<P>
There is a Cervantes research center at Nanjing University.
</P>
</TEXT>
