<HEADLINE> Mobile Phone Users in Beijing Top 470,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Expanded service coverage and
several price cuts have led to rapid increases in the number of
mobile phone subscribers in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Beijing Wareless Telecommunications Bureau
show that 180,000 new mobile phone users in the first eight months
of the year brought the total number in the city to 470,000,
including 340,000 GSM (Global service for mobile communication)
users and 130,000 cellular phone users.
</P>
<P>
The GSM network was launched in Beijing in April 1995. Many
mobile phone users prefer digital mobile phones because of their
high-quality, privacy and strong resistance against
interference. Subscribers also have easier access to those parties
called within China or overseas through automatic roaming.
</P>
<P>
Beijing is now linked to more than 2,000 Chinese cities and
counties and a number of foreign countries and regions, including
Singapore, Finland, Germany as well as Hong Kong and Macao,
through the automatic roaming service. 
</P>
</TEXT>
