<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Builds Industrial, Commercial Center in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 23 (Xinhua) -- An 80-million-Deutsche-Mark
center is being scheduled for 1999 in Shanghai to help Germany's
mid-sized and small enterprises enter rapidly growing Chinese
markets.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai German Industrial and Commercial Center will be
located in the Zhangjiang Hi-Tech Park in the Pudong New Area and
will serve as an overseas branch of the economic department of the
south German state of Bavaria.
</P>
<P>
The multi-purpose center, with 52,500 sq. m. of floor space,
will house offices, exhibition halls, training and entertainment
centers, restaurants, and storehouses.  
