<HEADLINE> Marine Protection Stressed in Zanzibar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The Zanzibari
government has stressed the need to conserve marine environment,
according to a report from the Isles of Tanzania reaching here
today.
</P>
<P>
The emphasis was announced by the Isles Minister for
Information, Tourism, Youth and Culture, Issa Mohamed Issa, when
he opened a three-day workshop on the artisanal fisheries sector
in Zanzibar on Monday.
</P>
<P>
He expressed concern over widespread destruction of marine
resources through bad fishing methods including dynamite fishing
which is being practised by unscrupulous fishermen, thus
destroying the environment.
</P>
<P>
Issa said that marine life in the Isles is being threatened by
such destructive tendencies at a time when demand for fish and
other sea products has reached an all time high due to the rapid
population increase.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the government needs to enact tougher and
appropriate legislation against the perpetrators of marine life
destruction.
</P>
<P>
Issa called for concerted efforts to protect marine resources
and enhance modern fishing techniques in a bid to ensure
increased catch to feed the growing population.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that his ministry will ensure that marine life is
appropriately developed, protected and conserved to consolidate
the Isles tourism industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
