<HEADLINE> Beijing-Paris Vintage Car Zooms off from Kathmandu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Ninety cars taking part in
the Beijing-Paris Classic and Vintage Car Rally got a rousing
send-off here Tuesday on the next stage of the historic event.
</P>
<P>
Each entrant was decorated with garlands as they left the
Birendra Conference Hall in Kathmandu and headed for southwestern
Kolahpur. From there, they will go to Nainital on Thursday in
India and to New Delhi.
</P>
<P>
The drivers arrived here from Lhasa on Saturday, on the rally
which will take them a gruelling, bumpy total of 15,924
kilometers, recreating the first and only previous such rally held
90 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of cheering and facinated Nepalese lined the route as
the cars left Kathmandu Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,000 to 3,000 visitors came and marvelled at the vintage
cars exhibited at the conference hall on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The rally set off from Beijing on September 6 and is scheduled
to arrive in Paris on October 18.
</P>
<P>
The route will also take in Turkey, Greece and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The vintage and classic cars taking part date from 1907 to the
newest model made in 1974. 
</P>
