<HEADLINE> 21 Hospitalized After Eating Poisoned Food in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-one people in a
village in Tabora Region, southwestern Tanzania, have been
admitted to hospital after eating some food suspected to have
been poisoned with DDT, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred on Monday morning after the victims'
families had bought maize flour in a shop, the report quoted
Regional Police Commander Ignas Mtana as confirming it.
</P>
<P>
The victims started vomiting immediately after they had taken
the maize meal, prepared from the suspected poisoned flour, Mtana
said.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary police investigation indicated that the shop owner
bought the maize from an unidentified person who had with him the
DDT sprayer, according to the Regional Police Commander. 
</P>
