<HEADLINE> Chiang Wei-kuo Dies in Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Former Senior Taiwan officer
Chiang Wei-Kuo died of illness in Taipei Monday night at the age
of 81.
</P>
<P>
According to Taiwan sources, Chiang had been suffering from
high blood pressure, chronic nephritis, diabetes and other
illness. He had been hospitalized since last November and his
health remained unstable.
</P>
<P>
Chiang was born in Fenghua, Zhejiang Province, in 1916 and
studied as a youth in Germany. He had served in the Kuomintang
military for 46 years.  
