<HEADLINE> Knights Technology to Set up Office in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 23 (Xinhua)-- The U.S.-based Silicon
Valley corporation Knights Technology Inc. (KT) is planning to set
up their first office in India in Mumbai (Bombay) to primarily
cater to the needs of their customers in the Far-East Asian
region.
</P>
<P>
"The Mumbai branch would be an extension of the California
office which will act as a vendor for reputed software systems,"
said Jese Ring, chief of KT Mumbai office.
</P>
<P>
KT is a 100 percent subsidiary of the U.S.-based semiconductor
equipment major Electrogras Inc. and is in the business of
designing, developing and subsequently marketing of systems
software.
</P>
<P>
"The choice of India as an extension in general and Mumbai in
particular are due to two specific reasons. Firstly, a lot of
technical manpower is readily available in Mumbai who are
extremely efficient and reasonably in terms of compensation.
Secondly, and more importantly, this is a strategic location for
other Asian countries who make up our customer base," Jese Ring
said.
</P>
<P>
Although Jese Ring has not disclosed Kt's initial investment in
India, other KT officials have asserted that the amount is about
one million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
