<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Export Growth up 18.72 Pc in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh has experienced an
export growth of 18.72 percent in the first month of the current
1997-98 fiscal year (starting from July 1, 1997), a well-informed
source said today.
</P>
<P>
The total export was 458 million U.S. dollars as against 385.27
million dollars in the same month of the last fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The export target for the 1997-98 fiscal year has been fixed at
five billion dollars against the previous year's income of 4.42
billion dollars, setting a 13 percent growth target in export
earnings, the source stated.
</P>
<P>
"Although we have exceeded the target, we have no time to waste
by indulging in dilly-dally practice, rather with this
achievement, we have to work enthusiastically to attain the whole
year's target," Commerce and Industries Minister Tofail Ahmed
said.
</P>
<P>
The minister asked the officials from the Export Promotion
Bureau to expedite their efforts to expand and diversify the
country's export items and the markets abroad.  
</P>
