<DOCNO> XIE19970923.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portable Artificial Heart Will Soon Come Out: Doctor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 22 (Xinhua) -- An Italian heart surgeon said
today that a portable artificial heart will soon be available.
</P>
<P>
During the 31st International Heart Diseases Meeting held today
in Milan, Italy, Alessandro Pellegrini said that current man-made
hearts are heavy and bulky and have to be connected to patients
through a number of tubes, leaving the patients no choice but to
lie on bed.
</P>
<P>
The Italian doctor said that a computerized and remote
controlled artificial heart, with no need for tubes to connect
with a patient, weighes three kilograms and can be carried on the
belt.
</P>
<P>
The instrument, with a 1.5 kilogram battery, can work for six
hours, Pellegrini said.
</P>
<P>
He claims the new device has already been tested on
sheep and operates satisfactorily.
</P>
<P>
The Italian surgeon said that he hoped the device could be
miniaturized so that it can eventually be implanted in the body of
a patient. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
