<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Stresses Friendly Ties with Cape Verde </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government
appreciates the efforts made by the government of Cape Verde to
stablize its international development, and values its friendly
relationship with China, said Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remarks during his talks with Premier Carlos
Veiga of Cape Verde, while attending the 52nd General Assembly of
the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
During their talks, Qian mentioned his previous visit to the
island nation in western Africa early this year, and expressed his
gratitude for the good will shown to him by the government and
people of Cape Verde.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese foreign minister also briefed the premier of the
African country on China's two major events this year: the
resumption of exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and it's
return to the motherland, and the convening of the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China, which outlined China's
strategic development plan into the next century.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his gratitude to the government of the
African country for its support of China by observing the "One
China" policy and its stand on human rights.
</P>
<P>
He also told Veiga that China is preparing for his impending
visit to Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The premier of Cape Verde said the people of his country hope
to be regarded as trust-worthy friends of the Chinese people, and
hope to establish a firm, long-term cooperative relationship with
China.
</P>
<P>
He also reiterated the stand of Cape Verde in pursuing the "One
China" policy, saying that his country will continue to support
China in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the meeting were Qin Huasun, the Chinese
ambassador to the United Nations, and Vice-Foreign Minister of
China Li Zhaoxing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
