<HEADLINE> Li Peng: Hong Kong's Future Will Be More Splendid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
predicted here today that Hong Kong's future will be more
splendid.
</P>
<P>
Li made this prediction this morning in his address at the
opening ceremony of the 1997 Annual Meetings of the Boards of
Governors of the World Bank Group and the International Monetary
Fund (IMF) in the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
As the head of government of the host country, Li extended his
warm congratulations to the meetings and sincere welcome to all
the delegates and honored guests.
</P>
<P>
He said that the meetings are the largest international
conference held in Hong Kong after its return to the motherland on
July 1 and the first such meetings ever held in China.
</P>
<P>
It is of great significance for promoting mutual understanding,
exchanges and cooperation among various parties, Li added.
</P>
<P>
Li quoted a Chinese saying which goes "Seeing it once is better
than hearing about it a hundred times."
</P>
<P>
"Now you are in Hong Kong, you can see with your own eyes that
the Chinese Government's basic policies of 'one country, two
systems', 'Hong Kong people administering Hong Kong' and 'a high
degree of autonomy' have been carried out in earnest, and the
government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
headed by Mr. Tung Chee Hwa is operating normally and effectively
in accordance with the 'Basic Law'," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed China's confidence that the SAR government and the
Hong Kong people will do a good job in running and building Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
It can be predicted that Hong Kong's future will be more
splendid, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, in its continued capacity as a free port and an
international financial, trade and shipping center, will play an
even more active role in strengthening the cooperation between
China's mainland and other countries in the economic field, Li
said.  
</P>
