<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Explains China's Goals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng explained
China's goals for economic and social development in the next 15
years at the opening ceremony of the 1997 Annual Meetings of the
World Bank and International Monetary Fund here today.
</P>
<P>
He said that the just-concluded 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) is an extremely important meeting
held at the turn of the century to carry forward the past and
break new ground for the future.
</P>
<P>
The Congress has "identified Deng Xiaoping Theory as our
guiding ideology after drawing upon the experience of past two
decades' reform, opening-up and socialist modernization drive," Li
said.
</P>
<P>
"In grasp of the situation, our central collective leadership
with President Jiang Zemin at the core is strong and enjoys the
support of the whole party and the entire population," he added.
</P>
<P>
Li said China's political situation is stable and the reform
and opening-up policies will not only remain unchanged but also
continue to develop and the cause pioneered by Deng Xiaoping will
not only go on, but also make even greater progress.
</P>
<P>
The period from now to the end of the first decade of the next
century, he went on, is crucial for China's modernization, during
which two tasks must be properly fulfilled.
</P>
<P>
One is to establish a rather complete structure of socialist
market economy and the other is to maintain a sustained, rapid and
sound development of the national economy, so as to lay a solid
foundation for basically realizing modernization by the middle of
the next century and building China into a prosperous, democratic
and culturally advanced socialist country.
</P>
<P>
China must actively promote a fundamental shift in both the
economic structure and the mode of economic growth, Li said.
</P>
<P>
China must continue to deepen reform, effect breakthroughs in
the reform and transformation of state-owned enterprises and the
diversification of the forms in which public ownership can be
realized, Li added.
</P>
<P>
China must also implement the policy of national rejuvenation
through science and education and the strategy of sustainable
development and achieve coordinated socio-economic development and
 overall social progress.
</P>
<P>
"These goals are magnificent and, given hard work, entirely
achievable because we have already found a right road of
development suited to China's national conditions, secured a
stable social and political situation, acquired quite a solid
material and technological base, and possessed a large market and
rich resources, and finally we have 1.2 billion industrious and
talented people," the premier said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
