<HEADLINE> Thai PM: Parliament Likely to Be Dissolved Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chavalit
Yongchaiyudh said Monday that the parliament is likely to be
dissolved in March or April next year before a snap election under
the new constitution in May, according to "the Bangkok Post"
today.
</P>
