himself in the two-day censure debate beginning on Wednesday, the
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The Thai parliament Wednesday will open a no-confidence debate
launched by the opposition, who accused Chavalit of mis-managing
the country's economy.
</P>
<P>
Chavalit and his coalition partners reportedly will have to
defend them from the opposition's attacks on economic issues and
corruption.  
