<HEADLINE> Li Peng Reiterates China's Policy of Opening-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng stated here
today that China will unswervingly carry out its policy of
opening-up.
</P>
<P>
He said that China will work energetically to embrace the world
by continuing to improve its all-directional, multi-layered and
extensive opening pattern.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the Annual Meetings of the
World Bank and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) at Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center, Li said that the economic
development of China is closely linked with that of the world.
</P>
<P>
A prosperous Chinese economy needs a substantial absorption of
advanced technologies, capital and management expertise from
abroad, he added.
</P>
<P>
To meet the needs under the new situation of reform, opening-up
and economic development, the Chinese government has decided to
further lower its tariff level by 26 percent in general and adopt
preferential policies on the access of new and high-tech equipment
and practical advanced technologies to China, Li said.
</P>
<P>
China's vast market and enormous growth potential will
undoubtedly provide even more opportunities for its cooperation
partners and instill fresh vigor into global and regional economic
development, he added.  
