<HEADLINE> Beijing Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- All Beijing-based major
newspapers gave prominence to the full text of the Constitution of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), whose amendments were approved
by the 15th National Party Congress on September 18.
</P>
<P>
The revisions of the Party Constitution mainly focused on more
explicitly defining Deng Xiaoping Theory as the guiding ideology
of the Party.
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin met with Finnish President Martti
Ahtisaari in Beijing Monday. It was President Jiang's first
meeting with a foreign head of state since the 15th National Party
Congress, at which he was again elected General Secretary of the
CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Li Peng and Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji met with Chief
Executive Tung Chee Hwa and other ranking officials of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) in Hong Kong Monday.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li noted that the HK SAR government is now operating
well, and assured Chief Executive Tung of the central government's
support to the government of the HK SAR.
</P>
<P>
-- Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji delivered a keynote speech in Hong
Kong Monday at a seminar sponsored by the World Bank on China's
economic development prospects in the 21st century, saying that
China will continue to follow unswervingly the opening-up policy
and march to the world even more confidently.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Chinese National People's Congress
(NPC) Standing Committee, met in Beijing Monday with Gabon's
Defense Minister Idriss Ngari.
</P>
<P>
-- The Standing Committee of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) held
its 22nd meeting here Monday, placing the study and implementation
of the guidelines of the 15th National Party Congress at the top of
the agenda.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese mainland will hold an investment forum in Hong
Kong from October 7 to 11, at which a total of 29 provinces and
municipalities will propose 889 projects ranging from agriculture
through manufacturing to potential foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
-- China is expected to hold an International Co-operation
Conference on Environmental Protection Projects on November 20-21
in Beijing to popularize the country's strategy, policies and
action plan on environmental pollution control. 
</P>
