<HEADLINE> Booming State-Owned Enterprises in China's Guangdong Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 23 (Xinhua) -- State-owned enterprises in
south China's Guangdong Province are maintaining a strong growth
momentum and gaining overall strength, a recent seminar on reform
and development of the province's state-run firms has indicated.
</P>
<P>
Currently, of the total 968 billion yuan in assets of the
province's industrial firms, 426 billion yuan worth of assets
belong to enterprises that are owned or held by the State.
</P>
<P>
Public ownership makes up 65 percent of the economy of
Guangdong, and it dominates basic and vital industries such as
energy, transportation, communications, power and metallurgy,
according to Vice-Governor Zhong Qiquan.
</P>
<P>
He said the fast growth of state-owned enterprises contributed
a great deal to the rise of Guangdong's total industrial output
from sixth in the nation to second.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, the growth of industrial output
of state-owned enterprises rose by 9.23 percent, while their
average annual growth in the Eighth Five-Year Plan period
(1991-1995) was nine percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
