<HEADLINE> Exhibition Featuring Coatings to Be Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 23 (Xinhua) -- An international exhibition
showcasing the latest development of the coatings industry will be
held in Beijing Agricultural Exhibition Hall from October 8-10,
"China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
Some 60 domestic and overseas enterprises will attend the fair,
which will be accompanied by a series of technical lectures given by
industry experts starting from October 7.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is organized by China National Coatings Industry
Association (CNCIA) and the Chemical Industry Sub-Council under
China Council for Promotion of International Trade (CCPIT).
</P>
<P>
China produced 1.5 million tons of coatings of various kinds
last year, ranking the fifth worldwide.
</P>
<P>
CNCIA forecast that by the year 2000, the demand for coatings
for industrial use will reach 700,000 tons, demand for building
sector will stand at 905,000 tons and demand for coatings of other
special functions such as anti-erosion road signals is expected to
hit 300,000 tons. 
</P>
