<HEADLINE> Polish Vote for 2006 Winter Olmypics Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Residents of Poland's mountain
resort of Zakopane have voted in a referendum to bid for the venue
of the 2006 winter Olympic Games, according to the local news on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 83 percent of Zakopane people who cast a vote in
Sunday's three-question referendum favoured the games, which are
opposed by environmentalists, while 79 percent said the event
would help the region's development.
</P>
<P>
However, Wojciech Gasienica Byrcyn, director of the local Tatra
National Park opposes the project which he says would devastate
Poland's forested southern mountain region.
</P>
<P>
Anyway, the Olympic bid is keenly supported by President
Aleksander Kwasniewski. 
</P>
