<HEADLINE> Spaniards Goes Through at Romanian Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Third seed Alberto
Berasategui of Spain struggled hard to outplay unseeded Romanian
Dinu Pescariu on Monday in the first round of the
475,000-U.S.-Dollar Romanian tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Berasategui, world-ranked 28th, needed two hours to beat his
tough opponent 6-3, 1-6, 7-6 (9-7).
</P>
<P>
The match became dramatic in the last set. Berasategui
struggled with long, hard shots while Pescariu centered his attack
near the net. The match went to a tie-break, where Pescariu lost
9-7 with several unforced errors.
</P>
<P>
Berasategui won the tournament last year against countryman
Carlos Moya.
</P>
<P>
In other two matches Monday, fourth-seeded Albert Portas of
Spain beat countryman Alberto Martin 4-6, 7-6 (7-5), 6-4 while
eight-seeded Karim Alami of Morocco lost to Spaniard Francisco
Clavet 3-6, 3-6.
</P>
<P>
The tournament's top-seeded Spaniards, Carlos Moya and Alex
Corretja, go into action later this week. 
</P>
