<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greek Economist Hails CPC's 15th Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 22 (Xinhua) -- A famous Greek economist today
hailed the 15th congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
which ended in Beijing on Friday, as an event of "very great
significance" in the modern history of China.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with Xinhua today, Marios
Nikolinakos, director of the institute for the study of the Greek
economy, said that the CPC congress consolidates the reforms
initiated by the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping and creates the
basis for a continuing course towards a big economic and political
power in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He said that the new Chinese leadership with President Jiang
Zemin as the core will be an almost absolute unanimity in the
leadership which is "a strong factor for its future efficacity and
the favorable climate expected, within which developments will
occur."
</P>
<P>
The conclusions reached and the decisions taken by the Congress
seem to be "of extreme importance" in respect both to the economic
development of the country and the radical changes to be carried
out in regard to structures and institutions as well as to the
position to be taken by China in the world scene.
</P>
<P>
A big country like China, he noted, is thus expected to play a
leading political role in the future not only in Asia but also in
the whole world.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Chinese economy will be further integrated
into the world economy by an increased import of foreign capital
to be established in China in the form of joint-ventures or on its
own, bringing with it modern technology and know how. Besides,
Chinese exports are expected to increase together with a tendency
of foreign economic expansion through Chinese investments abroad
in the form of joint-ventures or of Chinese enterprises on their
own.
</P>
<P>
As a consequence of the expected economic achievements, China's
political role at an international level will gain gradually
importance, thus offering a balance of forces in the world, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that China and Greece can take advantage and benefit
mutually from all-round cooperation between the two countries,
which is not only good for them but also conducive to the
development of the world economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
