<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FIFA TV to Go On Air Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- FIFA will produce its own
weekly television magazine program beginning next year, the world
soccer governing body said in Zurich on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The FIFA TV series, which will be produced by ISL television
productions, will include action and updates from international
competitions, coverage of World Cup qualifying matches, player
profiles, features, some of which will include footage never
previously shown, as well as commentary on current issues.
</P>
<P>
In a press release, FIFA general secretary Sepp Blatter said:
"FIFA TV will be the first genuinely international football
magazine program, which will balance coverage of the key issues
affecting major football markets with the progress of the
developing football nations."
</P>
<P>
Each of the 50 episodes will be 26 minutes long. The first will
be shown next January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
