<HEADLINE> Kamil Idris of Sudan Elected New WIPO Director-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Mr Kamil Idris of Sudan has
been elected as Director-General of the World Intellectual
Property Organization (WIPO) at its general assembly beginning
here today.
</P>
<P>
Idris will replace Mr Arpad Bogsch of the United States to be
WIPO's new director-general on December 1. Bogsch has been at the
post since 1973. 
</P>
</TEXT>
