<HEADLINE> IBM Leads Blue Chips, But Dow Fails to Push above 8,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 22 (Xinhua) -- IBM led the blue-chip sector
Monday, but the Dow Jones industrial average came up shy again on
its route to surge back above 8,000.
</P>
<P>
The Dow, which bobbed above 8,000 several times during the
session, rose 79.56 points to 7,996.83.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a 13-to-9 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where NYSE volume totaled 490.26 million
shares as against 630.54 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 4.92 to 955.43, and
the NYSE composite index rose 2.60 to 499.16, beating August 6's
record close of 497.00.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 rose 1.81 to 448.98; the Nasdaq composite index
rose 9.10 to 1,689.46 for its third straight record close; and the
American Stock Exchange composite index rose 3.00 to 689.94 to set
its seventh consecutive closing high.
</P>
<P>
The Dow, which has been down as much as 8 percent from August
6's record close of 8,259.31, hasn't finished a day above 8,000
since August 20.  
</P>
</TEXT>
